<Link id="l01390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1390"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Emitted = 0; Emitted != <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a>;) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1391"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Remaining = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a> - Emitted;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1392"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The size of our partial emission must be a power of two less than</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1393"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Size.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1394"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> EmissionSize = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ae22967d11b695d268992470debfae4b2">llvm::bit&#95;floor</a>(std::min(Remaining, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a> - 1));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1395"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Calculate the byte offset of our partial emission taking into account</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1396"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the endianness of the target.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1397"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ByteOffset =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1398"><span class="doxyHighlight">          IsLittleEndian ? Emitted : (Remaining - EmissionSize);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1399"><span class="doxyHighlight">      uint64&#95;t ValueToEmit = IntValue &gt;&gt; (ByteOffset &#42; 8);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1400"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We truncate our partial emission to fit within the bounds of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1401"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// emission domain.  This produces nicer output and silences potential</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1402"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// truncation warnings when round tripping through another assembler.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1403"><span class="doxyHighlight">      uint64&#95;t Shift = 64 - EmissionSize &#42; 8;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1404"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(Shift &lt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;cast&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">uint64&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">&gt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1405"><span class="doxyHighlight">                         std::numeric&#95;limits&lt;unsigned long long&gt;::digits) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1406"><span class="doxyHighlight">             </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;undefined behavior&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1407"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ValueToEmit &amp;= ~0ULL &gt;&gt; Shift;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1408"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mcasmstreamer-cpp-/mcasmstreamer/#a11156cb1f872cbe35d40c6f36a21d56f">emitIntValue</a>(ValueToEmit, EmissionSize);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1409"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Emitted += EmissionSize;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1410"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1411"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1412"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1415"><span class="doxyHighlight">  OS &lt;&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/directive">Directive</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1416"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mctargetstreamer">MCTargetStreamer</a> &#42;TS = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcstreamer/#a901607e60c20148ae701b6e8f43b4647">getTargetStreamer</a>()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
